<TEXT>

Ford announces deep production cuts in response to growing losses

<TIMEX3 tid="t1" type="DATE" value="2006-08-19">August 19, 2006</TIMEX3>

Ford has announced sweeping cuts of 21%(168,000 units )in its US and Canadian production, resulting in the partial closure of ten of its plants during <TIMEX3 tid="t2" type="DATE" value="2006-Q4">the fourth quarter</TIMEX3>.

The measure comes on top of existing turnaround plans announced in <TIMEX3 tid="t3" type="DATE" value="2007-01">January</TIMEX3>, in which 25,000 to 30,000 positions should be cut and 14 plants closed by <TIMEX3 tid="t4" type="DATE" value="2012">2012</TIMEX3>.

Ford is the world's third-largest automaker and the U.S.'s second-largest.

However it has in <TIMEX3 tid="t5" type="DURATION" value="PXY">recent years</TIMEX3> been struggling with poor profitability and shrinking market shares.

